# Models Directory

This directory contains trained model weights.

## Files

- `autoencoder_best.pth` - Best model checkpoint during training (auto-saved)
- `autoencoder_final.pth` - Final model after training completion

## Usage

```python
from src.autoencoder import ImprovedAutoencoder
import torch

# Load model
model = ImprovedAutoencoder(latent_dim=512)
model.load_state_dict(torch.load('models/autoencoder_best.pth'))
model.eval()
```

## Note

Model files are excluded from git (see `.gitignore`) due to size.
Pre-trained models are available via Google Drive (see main README).
